<inglise> of 20 December 1999 derogating from Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90 laying down detailed rules for granting private storage aid for pigmeat </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2713/1999, millega s&auml;testatakse erand m&auml;&auml;rusest (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90, millega kehtestatakse sealiha eraladustusabi andmise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad 20. detsember 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2759/75 of 29 October 1975 on the common organisation of the market in pigmeat(1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3290/94(2), and in particular Article 7(2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. oktoobri 1975. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2759/75 sealihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 3290/94, (2) eriti selle artikli 7 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Article 4(1) of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90 of 27 November 1990 laying down detailed rules for granting private storage aid for pigmeat(3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3533/93(4), stipulates that placing in storage must be completed not later than 28 days after the date of conclusion of the contract. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) komisjoni 27. novembri 1990. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 (milles s&auml;testatakse sealiha eraladustusabi andmise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 3533/93 (4)) artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 1 on ette n&auml;htud, et lattu paigutamine tuleb l&otilde;petada hiljemalt 28 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast lepingu s&otilde;lmimist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 of that Regulation defines the primary requirements to be complied with by operators. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 5 m&auml;&auml;ratletakse esman&otilde;uded, mida peavad t&auml;itma ettev&otilde;tjad. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 of that Regulation stipulates that the aid may be reduced or not paid if the quantity actually stored during the contractual storage period is less than the contractual quantity; </inglise>
<eesti> Selle m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 6 s&auml;testatakse, et abi v&otilde;ib v&auml;hendada v&otilde;i mitte v&auml;lja maksta, kui lepinguj&auml;rgsel ladustamisajal tegelikult ladustatud kogus on lepinguj&auml;rgsest kogusest v&auml;iksem; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Commission Decisions 1999/551/EC(5), as amended by Decision 1999/601/EC(6), and 1999/640/EC(7) lay down measures to protect certain products of animal origin intended for human or animal consumption from contamination by dioxin; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) komisjoni otsustes 1999/551/E&Uuml;, (5) muudetud otsusega 1999/601/E&Uuml;, (6) ja 1999/640/E&Uuml; (7) s&auml;testatakse meetmed teatavate loomse p&auml;ritoluga ja inim- v&otilde;i loomatoiduks etten&auml;htud toodete kaitsmiseks dioksiiniga saastumise eest; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) a small number of operators who concluded private storage contracts pursuant to Commission Regulation (EC) No 2042/98 of 25 September 1998 on special conditions for the granting of private storage aid for pigmeat(8), as amended by Regulation (EC) No 2619/98(9), have not been able to respect their contractual commitments because of the protection measures linked to the contamination by dioxin of certain products intended for human consumption and the slaughtering ban imposed by the Belgian authorities; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) teatavate inimtoiduks etten&auml;htud toodete suhtes v&otilde;etud ja dioksiinisaastet k&auml;sitlevate kaitsemeetmete t&otilde;ttu ning Belgia p&auml;devate asutuste kehtestatud tapakeelu t&otilde;ttu ei ole m&otilde;ned ettev&otilde;tjad, kes on s&otilde;lminud eraladustuslepingud vastavalt komisjoni 25. septembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 2042/98 (sealiha eraladustusabi andmise eritingimuste kohta, (8) muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2619/98 (9)), suutnud t&auml;ita oma lepingulisi kohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) because of those measures some or all of the quantities put into storage have been excluded from the grant of aid owing to the results of polychlorinated biphenyl (PCB) analyses or owing to the absence of evidence that the meat is of sound and fair merchantable quality in accordance with Article 2(2) of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) seoses nende meetmetega ei anta osa v&otilde;i k&otilde;ikide ladustatud koguste suhtes abi pol&uuml;kloor-bifen&uuml;&uuml;li anal&uuml;&uuml;si tulemuste t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i seet&otilde;ttu, et puuduvad t&otilde;endid liha veatu ja standardse turustuskvaliteedi kohta vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artikli 2 l&otilde;ikele 2; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) if operators are not to be disproportionately penalised in the light of the above quite exceptional circumstances, the rules normally applicable in such circumstances, as laid down in Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90, should not be applied; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) ei tuleks kohaldada sellistel juhtudel tavap&auml;raselt kohaldatavaid m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 s&auml;testatud reegleid, et ettev&otilde;tjaid eespool nimetatud erandlike asjaolude t&otilde;ttu &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;raselt ei karistataks; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Pigmeat, </inglise>
<eesti> 6) k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las sealihaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> By derogation from Article 4(1) of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90, operators who have concluded private storage contracts pursuant to Regulation (EC) No 2042/98, but who have not been able to complete placing in storage as a result of difficulties linked to the protective measures imposed by Decision 1999/551/EC may have a further 21 days in which to complete such placing. </inglise>
<eesti> Erandina m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artikli 4 l&otilde;ikest 1 v&otilde;ivad ettev&otilde;tjad, kes on s&otilde;lminud eraladustuslepingud vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 2042/98, kuid ei ole otsusega 1999/551/E&Uuml; v&otilde;etud kaitsemeetmetega seotud raskuste t&otilde;ttu suutnud lattu paigutamist l&otilde;petada, saada lattu paigutamise l&otilde;petamiseks ajapikendust 21 p&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The securities lodged under Regulation (EC) No 2042/98 in respect of private storage aid applications with a view to the conclusion of private storage contracts for which the primary requirement within the meaning of Article 5 of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90 could not be complied with because of the protective measures imposed by Decision 1999/640/EC and the slaughtering ban imposed by the Belgian authorities shall be released for the quantities not actually stored. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 2042/98 seoses eraladustuslepingute s&otilde;lmimiseks tehtud eraladustusabi taotlustega esitatud tagatised, mille esman&otilde;uet m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artiklis 5 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses ei ole saadud otsusega 1999/640/E&Uuml; v&otilde;etud kaitsemeetmete ja Belgia asutuste kehtestatud tapakeelu t&otilde;ttu t&auml;ita, tagastatakse nende koguste ulatuses, mida tegelikult ei ole ladustatud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> By derogation from Article 6 of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90, if the quantity actually stored under Regulation (EC) No 2042/98 during the contractual storage period is lower than the contractual quantity because of the protective measures imposed by Decision 1999/640/EC and the slaughtering ban imposed by the Belgian authorities, the aid shall be paid for the quantity actually stored. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui lepinguj&auml;rgse ladustusaja jooksul vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 2042/98 tegelikult ladustatud kogus on otsusega 1999/640/E&Uuml; v&otilde;etud kaitsemeetmete ja Belgia asutuste kehtestatud tapakeelu t&otilde;ttu lepinguj&auml;rgsest kogusest v&auml;iksem, makstakse erandina m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artiklist 6 abi tegelikult ladustatud koguse eest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> By derogation from Article 6(3) of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90, where some or all of the quantities stored under Regulation (EC) No 2042/98 have been excluded from the grant of aid owing to the results of PCB analyses stipulated by Decision 1999/640/EC or requested by the competent authorities pursuant to Article 2(2) of Regulation (EEC) No 3444/90, the aid shall be paid, where appropriate, for the quantity which has not been excluded because of those results. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui osa v&otilde;i k&otilde;ikide vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 2042/98 ladustatud koguste puhul ei antud abi otsusega 1999/640/E&Uuml; s&auml;testatud v&otilde;i vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artikli 2 l&otilde;ikele 2 p&auml;devate asutuste taotletud pol&uuml;kloor-bifen&uuml;&uuml;li anal&uuml;&uuml;si tulemuste t&otilde;ttu, makstakse erandina m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3444/90 artikli 6 l&otilde;ikest 3 vajaduse korral abi koguse puhul, mida ei ole j&auml;etud abist ilma anal&uuml;&uuml;si tulemuste t&otilde;ttu. </eesti>
<inglise> The security shall be released in its entirety. </inglise>
<eesti> Tagatis vabastatakse t&auml;ies ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall apply at the request of operators who can prove to the satisfaction of the competent authority that they have experienced the difficulties referred to in Articles 1, 2, 3 and 4 of this Regulation during performance of their private storage contracts concluded under Regulation (EC) No 2042/98 as a result of the protective measures imposed by Decisions 1999/551/EC and 1999/640/EC and the slaughtering ban imposed by the Belgian authorities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse nende ettev&otilde;tjate taotlusel, kes t&otilde;endavad p&auml;devat asutust rahuldavalt, et neil on vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 2042/98 s&otilde;lmitud eraladustuslepingute t&auml;itmise ajal otsustega 1999/551/E&Uuml; ja 1999/640/E&Uuml; v&otilde;etud kaitsemeetmete ning Belgia p&auml;devate asutuste kehtestatud tapakeelu t&otilde;ttu olnud k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklites 1, 2, 3 ja 4 osutatud raskusi. </eesti>
<inglise> In evaluating the situation referred to in the first paragraph the competent authorities shall use the commercial documents referred to in Article 1(2) of Council Regulation (EEC) No 4045/89(10) and the results of the PCB analyses referred to in Article 4. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses l&otilde;ikes osutatud olukorra hindamisel tuginevad p&auml;devad asutused eelk&otilde;ige n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 4045/89 (10) artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud &auml;ridokumentidele ja artiklis 4 osutatud pol&uuml;kloor-bifen&uuml;&uuml;li anal&uuml;&uuml;si tulemustele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 20 December 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 20. detsember 1999 </eesti>
